{"award_age":68.0,"bio_image":null,"category":"Economics","country":"United Kingdom","date_of_birth":"1904-04-08T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":"1989-05-20T00:00:00.000Z","gender":"male","image_urls":[],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Hicks","mini_bio":"<p>Sir <b>John Richard Hicks<\/b> (8 April 1904 \u2013 20 May 1989) was a British <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Economist\" title=\"Economist\">economist<\/a> and one of the most important and influential economists of the twentieth century. The most familiar of his many contributions in the field of economics were his statement of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Consumer_theory\" title=\"Consumer theory\" class=\"mw-redirect\">consumer demand theory<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Microeconomics\" title=\"Microeconomics\">microeconomics<\/a>, and the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/IS\/LM_model\" title=\"IS\/LM model\" class=\"mw-redirect\">IS\/LM model<\/a> (1937), which summarised a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Keynesian\" title=\"Keynesian\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Keynesian<\/a> view of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Macroeconomics\" title=\"Macroeconomics\">macroeconomics<\/a>. His book <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Value_and_Capital\" title=\"Value and Capital\">Value and Capital<\/a><\/i> (1939) significantly extended <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/General_equilibrium_theory\" title=\"General equilibrium theory\">general-equilibrium<\/a> and value theory. The <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Compensated_demand_function\" title=\"Compensated demand function\" class=\"mw-redirect\">compensated demand function<\/a> is named the Hicksian demand function in memory of him.<\/p><p>In 1972 he received the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Memorial_Prize_in_Economic_Sciences\" title=\"Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences\">Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences<\/a> (jointly) for his pioneering contributions to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/General_equilibrium_theory\" title=\"General equilibrium theory\">general equilibrium theory<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Welfare_economics\" title=\"Welfare economics\">welfare theory<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/John_Hicks#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"John Hicks","place_of_birth":"Warwick","place_of_death":"New York","text":"John Hicks , Economics, 1972","year":1972.0}